@startuml SearchBook
title Activity Diagram: Search Book

' Description:
' This activity diagram describes the process of searching for a book in the catalog.
' Steps:
' 1. Member initiates a search by entering search criteria (title, author, or category).
' 2. System validates that the search input is not empty.
' 3. If input is empty, system prompts the member to enter valid criteria.
' 4. System queries the catalog database using the provided criteria.
' 5. System checks whether matching results were found.
' 6. If no results are found, system notifies the member.
' 7. If results are found, system displays the list of matching books with availability status.
' 8. Member reviews the results and selects a book for more details.
' 9. System displays detailed information including title, author, ISBN, and copies available.
' 10. Activity ends.

|Member|
start
:Enter Search Criteria\n(title, author, or category);
|System|
:Validate Search Input;
if (Input Valid?) then (yes)
  :Query Catalog Database;
  if (Results Found?) then (yes)
    :Display Matching Books\nwith Availability;
    |Member|
    :Review Results;
    :Select a Book;
    |System|
    :Display Book Details\n(title, author, ISBN, copies);
    |Member|
    :View Book Details;
  else (no)
    :Notify No Results Found;
    |Member|
    :Informed - No Match;
  endif
else (no)
  :Prompt for Valid Input;
  |Member|
  :Re-enter Criteria;
endif
stop
@enduml
